==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spooney
<hw>Spoon"ey</hw> <pr>(-⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Weak-minded;
demonstratively fond; <as>as, <ex>spooney</ex> lovers</as>.</def>
<altsp>[Spelt also <asp>spoony.</asp>]</altsp>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spooney</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Spooney
<hw>Spoon"ey</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Spooneys</plw>
<pr>(-⟦icr⟧z)</pr>.</plu> <def>A weak-minded or silly person; one who is
foolishly fond.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There is no doubt, whatever, that I was a lackadaisical young
<qex>spooney</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Dickens.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spoonflower</ent>⟦br⟧
